	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				   Right now the Rogue's lead problem is they are underpowered warriors (they have Dual Wield and Second Attack, but far less hitpoints) and they traded that for backstabbing and the ability to handle locks and traps.  Of all the time I spent in Evequest, I've never seen a single trap or locked door (though I heard they exist) and so a Rogue's use becomes highly questionable.<BR>
   It's not as though they are useless however.  A Rogue can do a number of things a warrior can't (and vice versa), such as sneak, hide and backstab.  At higher levels a Rogue can be much nastier than a warrior because they can intimidate their opponents then backstab.  This can be fairly sick: Sneak.. find monster.. backstab for 3 digit damage.. intimidate it.. backstab for 3 digit damage again.. ect.  <BR>
   Lower levels they are in hell, were it not for one thing: Recently I read there are plans to fully impliment the Rogue skills Create Poison and Apply Poison.  This may well ressurect the rogue for all those who feel they are useless classes due to their picking locks and disarming trap skills being neigh worthless.<BR>
<BR>
   One thing to clear up, Everquest Rogues are not exactly what I would call D&amp;D Thieves because Rogues in Everquest can wear some pretty hefty armor, while your D&amp;D rogue is limited to leather.<BR>
<BR>
    One tip about playing Rogues, because the yare not really meant to endure damage you may be better off syphoning most of your starting points into Agility and avoiding damage the way monks do.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
